  <prompt>Edit `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/hooks/useBriefingNarration.ts`. Remove `hasFetchedRef.current` cache (lines ~111-131). Ensure refetch fires when `channels` or `actionsRefresh` change. Watch out for R3 PR #451 file overlap — check `notes/risks.md` R1.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. React hooks + effect-dependency refactoring; remove stale-cache bug in narration refetch.</role>
  <goal>`hasFetchedRef.current` cache removed from `useBriefingNarration.ts`. Refetch fires correctly when `channels` or `actionsRefresh` dependencies change. No stale-narration regression. `npm run build --workspace=@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` succeeds.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>R3 UAT defect: `hasFetchedRef.current` was added to prevent duplicate fetches but it persists across dependency changes, causing the narration to NOT refetch when underlying notification data (channels) updates. R4 FR-15 requires this cache to be removed so refetch happens on legitimate data changes. R3 PR #451 may touch the same file family — risks.md R1 must be checked first.</background>
